      <h1 class="display-4">IT Courses</h1>
      <p class="lead">In today’s world Information Technology (IT) has become the most fundamental need for proper functioning of human society. Be it running the banks or getting food from an eatery home-delivered, Information Technology has become a part and parcel of our lives. This dependence on Information Technology has given rise to the demand of learning and further innovation in this field as a result of which it has become one of the most popular fields in education and career. You can find IT specialisation in every branch of education, from IT & Software, Engineering, Aviation and Medicine to MBA and even Hospitality. In this technological era, the best career option for students in the present and immediate future is to become an Information Technology (IT) professional.

        Eligibility for Information Technology courses generally includes having completed their higher secondary education, such as completed class 10+2, with a focus on science or mathematics. Candidates are often required to have a minimum aggregate score in their qualifying examinations (50 percent in general), and some universities or institutes might specify additional subject requirements.</p>
     
 
   

 

